Include CPU Calculation Time in APEX Calculation

This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise and Unlimited editions where Consumer Goods Cloud is enabled.

Protect your system from reaching potential Apex CPU governance limit exceptions by incorporating a buffer in the calculation of sync execution time.

Configure the time to deduct from the org's governance limit for CPU utilization. When you configure this setting, the system includes the CPU calculation time during the calculation of the start time of sync transactions.

From the App Launcher, find and select Sync Configuration. Click Sync Settings. In the General Settings section, select the Calculate sync time with CPU time checkbox. This setting is disabled by default.
